# Architecture

## Monorepo Layout (planned)

```
streawman/
├── apps/
│   └── streawman-ui/         ← Next.js app (upload + watch in one)
├── services/
│   ├── core-api/             ← C++ Drogon — auth, users, video metadata, search, favorites
│   ├── uploader-api/         ← C++ Drogon — file ingestion + transcoding trigger only
│   └── watcher-api/          ← C++ Drogon — HLS manifest + segment serving only
├── infra/
│   ├── docker/               ← Dockerfiles per service
│   └── compose/              ← docker-compose files (dev / prod)
├── .github/
│   └── workflows/            ← GitHub Actions (one workflow per service + deploy)
├── tests/
│   └── load/                 ← k6 load and stress test scripts
├── docs/
│   ├── system-design/        ← diagrams, capacity estimates, flow docs
│   └── adr/                  ← Architecture Decision Records
└── AGENTS.md
```

## Data Flow

```
User (browser)
  │
  ├─→ Nginx (streawman.codigor.dev)
  │       │
  │       ├─→ /              → streawman-ui (Next.js SSR, port 3000)
  │       ├─→ /api/auth/     → core-api (port 8080)
  │       ├─→ /api/users/    → core-api (port 8080)
  │       ├─→ /api/videos/   → core-api (port 8080)
  │       ├─→ /api/upload/   → uploader-api (port 8081)
  │       └─→ /stream/       → watcher-api (port 8082)
  │
  ├─→ core-api (Drogon/C++)
  │       └─→ auth: JWT issue + refresh rotation (Redis)
  │       └─→ users, video catalog, search, favorites (PostgreSQL)
  │
  ├─→ uploader-api (Drogon/C++)
  │       └─→ saves raw file to disk
  │       └─→ enqueues transcode job in Redis → responds 202
  │       └─→ [thread pool] parallel FFmpeg per resolution → HLS segments
  │       └─→ updates PostgreSQL status → notifies user
  │
  ├─→ watcher-api (Drogon/C++)
  │       └─→ serves master.m3u8 + resolution playlists + .ts segments
  │       └─→ hls.js switches quality automatically
  │
  ├─→ PgBouncer (connection pool proxy, port 5432)
  │       └─→ PostgreSQL ← users, video metadata, transcode_jobs
  │               └─→ [Phase 2] read replica ← watcher-api + read paths
  └─→ Redis ← refresh tokens · transcode job queue · metadata cache
```

## Auth Flow

```
Login request
  └─→ validate credentials (PostgreSQL)
  └─→ issue access token (JWT, 15min, role claim, memory-only)
  └─→ issue refresh token (opaque, 30d, stored in Redis + HttpOnly cookie)

Refresh request
  └─→ validate refresh token in Redis
  └─→ mark old token as used, issue new refresh token (rotation)
  └─→ if reuse detected → revoke all tokens for user, force re-login

Per-request auth
  └─→ validate JWT signature + expiry
  └─→ check role claim against required permission
  └─→ no Redis/DB call needed per request (stateless access token)
```

